{{DEFAULTSORT:protected areas of Halsnaes Municipality}} [[Category:Halsnæs Municipality]] [[Category:Protected areas of Denmark by municipality|Halsnaes]]

'''Tephriphonolite''' is a [[mafic]] to [[intermediate composition|intermediate]] [[extrusive]] [[igneous rock]] in composition between [[phonotephrite]] and [[phonolite]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geology.sdsu.edu/how_volcanoes_work/Unusual%20lava.html|title=Unusual Lava Types|work=Strongly Alkaline Lavas|publisher=[[San Diego State University]]|accessdate=2016-09-11}}</ref> It contains 9 to 14% [[alkali]] content and 48 to 57% [[silica]] content (see [[TAS classification|TAS diagram]]).<ref>{{cite journal|title=Eruptive History and Chemical Evolution of the Precaldera and Postcaldera Basalt-Dacite Sequences, Long Valley, California: Implications for Magma Sources, Current Seismic Unrest, and Future Volcanism|last=Bailey|first=Roy A.|year=2004|page=17|publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]]}}</ref>

Tephriphonolite has been found, for example, at [[Colli Albani]] volcano, Italy<ref name="CampagnolaEtAl2016">{{cite journal | url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0009254116300122 | title=Crystallization kinetics and rheology of leucite-bearing tephriphonolite magmas from the Colli Albani volcano (Italy) | first=S. | last=Campagnola | first2=A.| last2=Vona | first3=C. | last3=Romano | first4=G. | last4=Giordano | journal=Chemical Geology | year=2016 | volume=424 | pages=12–29 | doi=10.1016/j.chemgeo.2016.01.012}}</ref> and in the Asuncion Rift, Paraguay.<ref name="VelázquezEtAl2011">{{cite journal | url=https://www.hindawi.com/journals/jgr/2011/946701/ | title=The Cretaceous Alkaline Dyke Swarm in the Central Segment of the Asunción Rift, Eastern Paraguay: Its Regional Distribution, Mechanism of Emplacement, and Tectonic Significance | first=V.F. | last=Velázquez | first2=C. | last2=Riccomini | first3=C. |last3=de Barros Gomes | first4=J. | last4=Kirk | journal=Journal of Geological Research | year=2011 | volume=2011 | doi=10.1155/2011/946701}}</ref>

